<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501354>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Lectotype (A), isolectotype (B), and remaining syntype (C, D) sheets of Artemisia neosinensis (= A. sinensis). A. Inset: portion of a leaf, abaxially arachnoid-tomentose. C. Inset a: portion of a leaf, adaxially tomentose; inset b: capitula, phyllaries abaxially arachnoid-tomentose." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501354/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501364>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Artemisia neosinensis in the wild [China, Yunnan, Yulong County (= Lijiang County), the type locality of A. neosinensis]. A. Habitat and habit. B. Rhizome and roots. C. Portions of stem (left: distal portion; right: proximal portion). D. Leaves. E. Adaxial side of leaf. F. Abaxial side of leaf. G. Portion of synflorescence. H. Capitula. I. Phyllaries (abaxial side). J. Receptacle. K. Marginal female florets. L. Disk florets." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501364/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501366>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Artemisia neosinensis in the wild (China, Yunnan, Ninglang County).A. Habitat and habit. B. Rhizome and roots. C. Portions of stem (left: distal portion; right:proximal portion).D. Leaves. E.Adaxial side of leaf. F.Abaxial side of leaf.G. Portion of synflorescence. H. Capitula. I. Phyllaries (abaxial side). J. Receptacle. K. Marginal female florets. L. Disk florets." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501366/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501382>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Lectotype (A), isolectotype (B), and remaining syntype (C, D) sheets of Artemisia strongylocephala var. sinensis f. virgata. A, B. H. Handel-Mazzetti 3104 (E, WU) from Ninglang County in Yunnan, belonging to A. neosinensis. C. G. Mussot 205 (P) from Kangding County in Sichuan, belonging to A. tangutica var. tomentosa. D. J.A. Soulié 640 (P) from Kangding County in Sichuan, belonging to A. tangutica var. tomentosa." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501382/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501380>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Correcteddistributionof Artemisia neosinensis(= A.sinensis; ●) andwrong distributionalrecords (■) duetomisidentifications of specimens. Black arrow indicates the type locality of A. neosinensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501380/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501388>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Specimens of Artemisia somae. S.T. Chiu et al. 3371 (HAST, PE) from Nantou County in Taiwan, China." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501390>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Syntype sheets of Artemisia tainingensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501390/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501392>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Artemisia tainingensis in the wild (China, Sichuan, Dawu County, the type locality).A. Habitat and habit. B. Rhizome and roots. C. Portions of stem (left: distal portion; right: proximal portion). D. Leaves. E.Adaxial side of leaf. F.Abaxial side of leaf.G. Portion of synflorescence. H. Capitula. I. Phyllaries (abaxial side). J. Receptacle. K. Marginal female florets. L. Disk florets." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6501392/files/figure.png" ;
